metadata.name: Tezumie #770
metadata.description:
Tezumie are interdimensional beings who seemingly spawn out of thin air. Tezumie are obsessed with Eating, fighting, and Collecting junk they find throughout the universe. Once a Token is minted, you will spawn your very own Tezumie! 

Beware, there is more to them than they let on. They are not Restricted to the blockchain, and you may notice strange things appearing and disappearing around you. You have been warned.

metadata.name: Floatrest #228
metadata.description:
Floating forests over the endless sky, where birds, trees, plants, roots, rocks and waterfalls share an ecosystem full of life and emotion.

You can see some rain clouds in the sky and the sun shining under the raindrops.

The earth is moving, the blocks are falling, but the trees are strong in their roots.

Welcome to 'Floatrest'.

----

# Features

- 7 tree palettes
- 17 different background colors
- 10 different terrain colors
- clouds
- vines
- roots
- plants
- waterfall
- birds
- sun / moon
- night
- dark mode
- monochromatic
- 2 different aspect ratios (square & portrait)
- Press "p" on live mode to save in PNG

This artwork requires processing power and is intended for laptops and desktops primarily. It may take some time to render.

----

July 2022, gpitombo

metadata.name: Cosmic Type #230
metadata.description:
Cosmic Type is a kinetic type experiment that explores both graphic space as structural and semantic agency. Inspired by the early pioneering work of the concrete poets such as Dom Sylvester Houédard, Ian Hamilton Finley and Steve McCaffe, the project is a play with letters, words and graphic form in the computational and generative space.

Each iteration gives you the possibility to discover a variety of visual form through exploring the system. Please explore your iteration with the key interactions below. It is hoped that you give the time to explore and observe. If you don't, you may end up with just a blank canvas. 

Thank you for collecting. 

Key Interactions

‘a’ activates forward motion on/off
‘b’ activates backward motion on/off
‘r’ rotates grid 45° [ rotates on key pressed]
‘f’ rotates the grid freely [ stops on key release ]
‘p’ switches grid scale on/off [ this can be CPU heavy on older machines ] 
‘g’ extra glyphs on/off
‘q’ return to the initial state 


Program written by Mark Webster
Font is copyright ©simonrenaud

areafour.xyz
@motiondesign_01

metadata.name: a house divided #26
metadata.description:
This piece reuses the same line drawing algorithm from 'this is where i draw the line', meant to emulate a marker drawing on paper.

In terms of composition, we start with a single square, which we divide into two rectangles, either horizontally or vertically. We then repeat this process some number of times for each of the resulting rectangles. Finally, we fill the rectangles by drawing them with lines. These lines
can be either straight or curved.

The collection of inks and papers has also been expanded from 'this is where i draw the line'. Collectors of that piece have been placed on the reserve list as a thank you for their support.

This piece was created using p5.js

metadata.name: Tezumie 1-1 #87
metadata.description:
Tezumie have found themselves in Dimension 1-1, the perfect place for an adventure!

-WARNING-
They may seem to be a cute companion to hang out in your browser, but DO NOT leave them there for extended periods.  

Side effects may include: Missing items in your household, odd behavior in pets, a strange odor, prolonged nightmares, restless leg syndrome, hearing colors, missing teeth, uncontrollable urges, existential crisis, temporary blindness, and a strong appetite for non-edible objects.

AgataPoison, Craigers , griza, iRyanBell, Jim the Bim, KilledByAPixel, Liam Egan, Littlesilver, lucky26, MarkKnol, ozzie, PersonChen, punevyr, and the creators of MIME x MIME.

-CONTROLS-
(W)-Toggle weather
(F)-Toggle frame 
(C)-Toggle cursor
(P)–Pause
(A)-Shrink
(D)-Grow
(SHIFT + S)-Save image
(SHIFT + G)-Save 4 frames that you can use to make a GIF, see “sketch.js” for further instructions.

Made in p5js.

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #146
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. “The Bugged Tree”’s code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren’t under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there’s a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: Crypt-o-Show #58
metadata.description:
Crypt-o-show is a parody art gallery generator, inspired by a very disappointing and comical NFT show produced by Christies. The infamous show displayed Artblock works on unsuitable screens, installed closely together, over a large squiggle on the wall. The generator creates a little gallery with a random selection of artworks that parody AB pieces – these are used as features in this work – forming a mini collection of collectibles. 

Crypt-o-show is a form of ‘institutional critique’ through generative art, and about generative art, poking fun at the both the market for on-chain generative artwork collections made addictive through their lottery mechanics, as well as mocking the traditional auction house and its blundering and inelegant support for these new digital practices. 

"The saddest thing you'll see today is, once again, brought to you by Christie's."
- @MPtherealmvp (twitter.com/MPtherealmvp/status/1442917552871526401)

Initial idea tweeted on 2/9/21 (twitter.com/M_PF/status/1443129233472212992)

metadata.name: Obscured by Clouds #2
metadata.description:
This artwork is an attempt to create a painterly texture and to keep the focus on just the paint rather than any object it fills. It's coded in p5.js and uses overlapping translucent shapes to create the texture.

Best viewed on a screen bigger than a mobile phone, while listening to this track called 'Obscured by Clouds' by Pink Floyd: https://open.spotify.com/track/3c8LKbUsjW9lMYQzVScXQT
Press 's' to save the image

Credits:
 - Technique is inspired by this essay by Tyler Hobbs: https://tylerxhobbs.com/essays/2020/how-to-hack-a-painting
 - The name of the artwork is a tribute to my favourite band
